<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="68066275">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>In case you are stuck with error or your array doesn't sort you can give this a try as this works for me-</p>
<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">usort</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$blogusers</span>,function (<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>, <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>)
{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">strcmp</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$a</span>[<span class="hljs-string">"display_name"</span>], <span class="hljs-variable">$b</span>[<span class="hljs-string">"display_name"</span>]);
});
</code></pre>
    </div>
    <div class="mt24">
        <div class="d-flex fw-wrap ai-start jc-end gs8 gsy">
            <time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2021-06-21 10:28:59Z"/>
            <div class="flex--item mr16" style="flex: 1 1 100px;">
                


<div class="js-post-menu pt2" data-post-id="68066275" data-post-type-id="2">

